Scientific Games Corp (SGMS) Shares Bought by Ameriprise Financial Inc.

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 

Ameriprise Financial Inc. raised its position in Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) by 5.5% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The firm owned 268,535 shares of the technology company’s stock after buying an additional 13,899 shares during the period. Ameriprise Financial Inc. owned about 0.30% of Scientific Games Corp worth $6,351,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
A number of other institutional investors have also recently bought and sold shares of SGMS. Canada Pension Plan Investment Board bought a new position in shares of Scientific Games Corp during the first quarter worth approximately $11,026,000. Norges Bank acquired a new position in shares of Scientific Games Corp during the fourth quarter valued at about $5,808,000. Acadian Asset Management LLC acquired a new position in shares of Scientific Games Corp during the first quarter valued at about $8,710,000. Castleark Management LLC acquired a new position in shares of Scientific Games Corp during the fourth quarter valued at about $3,993,000. Finally, BNP Paribas Arbitrage SA increased its position in shares of Scientific Games Corp by 1,714.7% in the first quarter. BNP Paribas Arbitrage SA now owns 210,690 shares of the technology company’s stock valued at $4,983,000 after buying an additional 199,080 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 61.38% of the company’s stock. 




Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ SGMS) remained flat at $26.85 during midday trading on Friday. 1,275,099 shares of the stock were exchanged. The stock has a 50 day moving average price of $25.67 and a 200-day moving average price of $21.95. The company’s market capitalization is $2.38 billion. Scientific Games Corp has a 12 month low of $8.07 and a 12 month high of $27.40. 


 Get Scientific Games Corp alerts:



Scientific Games Corp (NASDAQ:SGMS) last posted its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, April 27th. The technology company reported ($0.92) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of ($0.74) by $0.18. The company had revenue of $725.40 million for the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $706.74 million. Scientific Games Corp’s revenue for the quarter was up 6.4% on a year-over-year basis. On average, equities analysts expect that Scientific Games Corp will post ($2.38) EPS for the current fiscal year. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION WARNING: This report was posted by BNB Daily and is the property of of BNB Daily. If you are reading this report on another site, it was copied illegally and republished in violation of United States & international copyright and trademark law. The original version of this report can be viewed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/22/ameriprise-financial-inc-buys-13899-shares-of-scientific-games-corp-sgms-updated-updated.html. 
Several research firms have issued reports on SGMS. Telsey Advisory Group upped their price target on Scientific Games Corp from $20.00 to $24.00 and gave the company a “market perform” rating in a report on Friday, April 28th. BidaskClub downgraded shares of Scientific Games Corp from a “strong-buy” rating to a “buy” rating in a research note on Wednesday, July 5th. Zacks Investment Research raised shares of Scientific Games Corp from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $30.00 target price on the stock in a research note on Thursday. Stifel Nicolaus reissued a “hold” rating and set a $24.00 target price on shares of Scientific Games Corp in a research note on Friday, July 14th. Finally, ValuEngine raised shares of Scientific Games Corp from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Friday, June 2nd. Five investment analysts have rated the stock with a hold rating and four have given a buy rating to the company’s stock. The stock has an average rating of “Hold” and a consensus price target of $24.50.
In other Scientific Games Corp news, Director Michael Gavin Isaacs sold 154,951 shares of the company’s stock in a transaction dated Tuesday, May 2nd. The shares were sold at an average price of $22.81, for a total transaction of $3,534,432.31. Following the sale, the director now directly owns 110,542 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $2,521,463.02. The sale was disclosed in a legal filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is available through this link. 42.03% of the stock is currently owned by corporate insiders. 
Scientific Games Corp Company Profile
Scientific Games Corporation is a developer of technology-based products and services and associated content for the gaming, lottery and interactive gaming industries. Its segments include Gaming, Lottery and Interactive. Its portfolio includes gaming machines and game content, casino management systems, table game products and services, instant and draw-based lottery games, server-based gaming and lottery systems, sports betting technology, lottery content and services, loyalty and rewards programs, interactive gaming and social casino solutions. 

 
