Other Dow Jones











Nasdaq closes at record as tech stocks shake off broader weakness

Jul. 24, 2017 at 4:45 p.m. ET
by Barbara Kollmeyer









Scientific Games Corp. shares soaring after revenue beat 
Shares of Scientific Games Corporation  were soaring 22.%% Monday afternoon after the company beat second-quarter revenue expectations. Scientific Games, which provides products and services that power lotteries and gambling-related games, reported a net loss of $39.1 million, or a loss of 44 cents per share, compared to a loss of $51.7 million, or 59 cents per share, in the year-earlier period. Analysts surveyed by FactSet expected a loss per share of 41 cents. Revenue was $766.3 million, up from $729.2 million in the year-earlier period and above the FactSet consensus of $748.6 million. Shares of Scientific Games have gained 50% in the past three months and 137% year-to-date, compared with the S&P 500's  gains of 4% and 10% respectively. 

Jul. 24, 2017 at 12:58 p.m. ET
by Caitlin Huston









Scientific Games Corp. shares soaring 22.5%
Scientific Games Corp. shares soaring 22.5%

Jul. 24, 2017 at 12:43 p.m. ET
by Caitlin Huston









Dow industrials nail first support, S&P 500 digests the technical breakout
U.S. stocks are slightly higher early Wednesday, digesting the mid-2017 technical breakout ahead of Thursday’s ECB policy directive, U.K. general election, and scheduled political testimony in the U.S.  Against this backdrop, the Dow Jones Industrial Average has effectively nailed first support (and drawn buyers), while the S&P 500’s corresponding pullback remains conspicuously flat.

Jun. 7, 2017 at 11:33 a.m. ET
by Michael Ashbaugh










Is this $1 billion scratch-card game everything that’s wrong with America?

May. 20, 2017 at 5:07 p.m. ET
by Quentin Fottrell










How to spend (and invest) Willy Wonka’s $1 billion scratch-off prize

May. 11, 2017 at 2:51 p.m. ET
by Jacob Passy









Instant game Willy Wonka Golden Ticket offers winner prizes up to $1 billion
Scientific Games Corp.  said Thursday that it is launching an instant game, Willy Wonka Golden Ticket, that will offer players the chance to win prizes up to $1 billion. Players "scratch" to win prizes as well as a chance to win a trip to Las Vegas to participate in the Willy Wonka Billion Dollar Challenge where winners will get cash prizes from $1,000 to $1 billion. The Billion Dollar Challenge is planned for May 2018. The game is available in 11 U.S. states, with Texas the first to launch in March, with tickets priced at $10. Georgia, Kentucky and Colorado are among the other states participating. Scientific Games shares are unchanged in premarket trading, but up 164% over the past year. The S&P 500 index  is up 16.2% for the last 12 months.

